**J.J. Cahill's Perspective**

You slam the newspaper down on your desk. The *Herald* headline screams: "LABOR MP BACKS US STRIKE AGAINST AUSTRALIAN EXPORTS."

Ward. That bloody fool Ward.

Your phone hasn't stopped ringing. Business donors furious. Catholic trade unionists asking if Labor has gone communist. Menzies already preparing a parliamentary ambush. And worst of all - the federal leadership calling for an explanation.

You pick up the phone and dial Ward's office.

"WARD! WHAT THE BLOODY HELL DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?!"

Ward's voice comes back defensive. "I'm standing with the workers, Jack. Someone has to—"

"STANDING WITH THE WORKERS?! You've just handed Menzies a bloody gift! 'Labor supports foreign strikes against Australian exports!' He'll dine out on this for months!"

"The debt arrangement—"

"I don't care about your anti-imperialist nonsense! The Right controls the numbers in NSW. You don't speak for Labor. You speak for yourself. And if you can't understand party discipline, maybe you need to find another party!"

You hang up. Your secretary peers in nervously.

"Sir, the Groupers are calling. They want an emergency meeting. They're demanding Ward be censured."

Of course they are. This is exactly the kind of thing Santamaria lives for.

**Cahill will now coordinate with the Groupers to contain the damage...**

